<Docs title="Development" description="Local development and VS Code debugging for Dep Beacon.">
  <h1>Development</h1>
  <p>
    Dep Beacon ships with VS Code Run and Debug profiles, workspace tasks, and a sample workspace so extension development starts from the editor.
  </p>

  <h2>First run</h2>
  <pre><code>pnpm install
pnpm run build
pnpm run package:extension</code></pre>

  <h2>VS Code Run and Debug</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open the `dep-beacon` folder in VS Code.</li>
    <li>Open Run and Debug.</li>
    <li>Choose `Dep Beacon: Extension (Build Once)` for the safest first launch.</li>
    <li>Choose `Dep Beacon: Extension (Watch)` after running the `vscode-dep-beacon: dev` task when actively editing the core or extension.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    The default debug target opens `examples/sample-workspace`, which contains regular dependencies, pnpm catalogs, overrides, and package extensions.
  </p>

  <h2>Useful tasks</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>`vscode-dep-beacon: build` builds the core engine and extension bundle.</li>
    <li>`vscode-dep-beacon: dev` starts core and extension watch tasks.</li>
    <li>`dep-beacon-docs: dev` starts the Astro docs site.</li>
    <li>`dep-beacon: validate` runs build, typecheck, tests, lint, and VSIX packaging.</li>
  </ul>
</Docs>
